Preparations for the swearing in of new Bungoma Governor Wycliffe Wangamati (pictured) on Monday next week are in top gear. County secretaryChiuli Murumba has saidthe function will cost Sh3 million. Initially the committee planned to use Sh14 million, but the budget was slashed to Sh8 million — then Sh3 million on the instruction of the new governor. The function will be held at Kanduyi Stadium. Speaking to the press in his office in Bungoma town on Wednesday, Murumba said the committee will ensure the function is done in a smooth manner. “We are going to have officers from the national government, one from Devolution ministry and another from intergovernmental technical committee together with county security team lead by county commissioner Joshua Chepchieng,” he said.  